        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 24 at 3:27PM EDT by NWS Detroit/Pontiac MI</headline>
        <description>At 327 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Lake Fenton, or near Fenton, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Fenton, Lapeer, Grand Blanc, Holly, Oxford, Burton, Hadley, Goodrich,
Ortonville, Metamora, Lake Fenton, Atlas, Rankin, Holly State
Recreation Area, and Thornville.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
